textBeforeTable: Chemical Composition   Ask a Question   AL-6XN alloy is identified by the Unified Numbering System (UNS) designation of N08367. AL-6XN alloy is an austenitic stainless steel alloy with high nickel, molybdenum, and nitrogen content. AL-6XN alloy has a face-centered cubic crystal structure similar to other austenitic stainless steels. The alloy is non-magnetic and its magnetic permeability remains low even after severe cold forming. AL-6XN alloy has exceptional resistance to chloride corrosion, pitting, crevice corrosion, stress corrosion cracking, and excellent general corrosion resistance to various acid, alkalis and salt solutions.
